      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The most forceful arguments against race-conscious hiring center on the principle of pure meritocracy, asserting that any preference based on race inherently introduces bias and undermines true competence. Critics argue that focusing on demographic goals inevitably forces companies to hire less qualified individuals simply to meet quotas, thereby lowering the overall standard of excellence. From this perspective, a strictly race-blind system ensures that the best talent, regardless of background, rises to the top, which they claim is the only way to maintain competitive advantage.",
